headline: How Recent Analyst Revisions Are Reframing The Banco BPM (BIT:BAMI) Investment Story
summary: Banco BPM’s fair value estimate has been nudged higher to €13.58 per share from €13.38, a €0.20 adjustment that lines up with recent target moves such as the €0.30 lift from JPMorgan. Behind this shift are updated assumptions around revenue growth and the discount rate, which bullish and bearish analysts alike are now building into their models while still reaching different conclusions on upside and execution risk.
